Insider Activity


Individual




Charles P. Cooley



Mr. Charles P. Cooley is Independent Director at KeyCorp, Independent Director at Modine Manufacturing Co., and Chairman at Hawken School. He is on the Board of Directors at KeyCorp, Modine Manufacturing Co., and Cleveland Institute of Music.
Mr. Cooley was previously employed as Chief Financial Officer & Senior Vice President by The Lubrizol Corp., an Assistant Treasurer-Corporate Finance by Atlantic Richfield Co., and Vice President-Finance by ARCO Products Co.
He received his undergraduate degree from Yale University and an MBA from the Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth.



